	<text>
		<body>
			<p>
				<persName ref="#ehri_et_szczucinska_dwojra">Dwojra Szczuczyńska</persName> Testimony (doc. 301/2)</p>
			<p>Original, manuscript, 2 pages, 210 x 295 mm, Polish language</p>
			<pb n="1" facs="EHRI-ET-ZIH3010002_01.jpg"/>
			<p><persName ref="#ehri_et_szczucinska_dwojra">Dwojra Szczuczyńska</persName>, residing in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/756135/warsaw.html">Warsaw</placeName>, tells about the <q>Hotel</q> for Jews that was set up by
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1159" type="subject">Germans</term> in cooperation with the Jewish
					<orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-350">Gestapo</orgName> men.</p>
			<p>In <date when="1943-05">May 1943</date>, the news came that Jews who were <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1149" type="subject">foreign citizens</term> could leave the country. This
				was a trap for Jews who were settled or in <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-262" type="subject"
					>hiding</term> on the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-373" type="subject">Aryan</term> side. There
				were (it was said) certificates at the <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-350">Gestapo</orgName> for
				Jews who had <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">died</term> in action, <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1159" type="subject">Germans</term> making it convenient for the Jews who
				had survived, sold <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1149" type="subject">citizenships</term> and with
				that underhanded method caught the naïve ones. <note type="gloss">There were two types of documents which were supposed to provide
					their holders security: certificates issued by British authorities, authorizing entry to Palestine, and the passports of the Latin
					American countries.</note>At the head of this scam was a Jewish <orgName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-350">Gestapo</orgName> officer named <persName
					ref="#ehri_et_skosowski_lolek">Lolek Skosowski</persName>, a resident of <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/3093133/lodz.html">Łódź</placeName> (who lived until the last minute in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/702550/lviv.html">Lwów</placeName> at <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/702550/lviv.html">4
					Teresy Street</placeName> and was <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">killed</term>
				by the party), who sacrificed his own <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">family</term>
				to underscore the trustworthiness of this program, having taken them out of the <placeName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_ghettos-513" type="ghetto">Łódź ghetto</placeName>.</p>
			<p>Naïve people were recruited at the <q>Hotel Polski</q> on Długa Street. At the gate there was an armed <foreign>guard
				[wacha]</foreign>, <note type="gloss">Wacha (German ‑ Wache) – guard post.</note> who kept order and chased away onlookers. The
				richest Jews fell victim to this, who would pay several hundred thousand <foreign xml:lang="pl">złotys</foreign> each for a
				certificate. They came with their fancy baggage. There was a restaurant and barber shop right there. The ladies and gentlemen felt as
				if they were on a fancy ship. A committee was formed <pb n="2" facs="EHRI-ET-ZIH3010002_02.jpg"/> from among the Jews, which took care
				of <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-327" type="subject">orphaned</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">children</term> who were allegedly supposed to leave
				for <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/6254930/palestine.html">Palestine</placeName>. Thanks to the <q>big-heartedness</q> of the
					<orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-350">Gestapo</orgName>, poor <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-327" type="subject">orphans</term> were accepted in exchange for payments
					<q>in-kind</q> and similar arrangements. <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-521" type="subject"
					>Transports</term> were sent depending on how many naïve people were taken in. There were three such <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-521" type="subject">transports</term>. The first was to <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/2967845/vittel.html">Wittel</placeName>
				<note type="gloss">Wittel – Vittel, a spa town in France. Group held in Vittel was then deported to the death camp at
					Auschwitz.</note>, from whence letter were even sent, the second went to <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/6559065/hannover-landeshauptstadt.html">Hannover</placeName>, the third and last to <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/756135/warsaw.html">Pawiak</placeName>. <note type="gloss">Further groups of residents of <q>Hotel
						Polski</q> were deported to the concentration camp at Bergen‑Belsen.</note></p>
			<p>After a while, there ceased to be any news. A card from <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/6559065/hannover-landeshauptstadt.html"
					>Hannover</placeName> came from one <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject"
				>woman</term>, written in an arranged code to her friends, which unmasked the enormity of the scam, namely the sentence <q>we are
					doing very well</q> was to mean the group’s <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-529" type="subject"
					>extermination</term>.</p>
			<p>The last <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-521" type="subject">transport</term> did not go far, only to the
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-669" type="subject">prison</term> known as <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/756135/warsaw.html">Pawiak</placeName>, hundreds of thousands of people were <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">killed</term>.</p>
			<p>The <q>hotel</q> scam caught about 3,000 people from the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-373"
					type="subject">Aryan</term> neighborhood. They were people who had every opportunity: they looked good, had <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-831" type="subject">living conditions</term>, and were <q>set up</q>,
				which means they had <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-943" type="subject">work</term> in various places
				(railroad, post office, fire department) and they had the possibility of surviving the period of <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1159" type="subject">German</term> barbarity.</p>
			<p><note type="gloss">[Signature:]</note><persName ref="#ehri_et_szczucinska_dwojra">Szczuczyńska</persName></p>
			<p><placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/765876/lublin.html">Lublin</placeName>, <date when="1944-09-04">September 4, 1944</date></p>
			<p>Collected by <persName ref="#ehri_et_asz_marek">M. Asz</persName></p>
